{Mr John Lenthall}has a family of six children who live in the Loundsley Green area.
{Catherine Lenthall}is six years old. She has approximately 35 hours of free time each week. Her main interests are playing chess, reading and playing the piano. She is very keen on{Non-stop {Cricket.}This is a team game which tries to get everyone involved. The{ {aim}of the game is to score runs by running between wickets. Unlike real cricket the batsman has to run whether he has hit the ball or not.
{Clare Lenthall}is seven years old. Her activities include playing games and musical instruments. As she is older than Catherine, Clare belongs to a local{Brownie pack.}
